@Chris I wasted about 2 minutes trying to find ISAAK / SKOR.

Definitely a Monday-level puzzle. 

AI slop has arrived in the NYT crossword puzzle! It had to happen at some point.

@Douglas Laycock

Would you like to tell us which clues made no sense, or do you just want to leaving it hanging there?

Or is this just a cry from the heart?

@Matt

I see three people who are willing to help someone who is either a newcomer or possibly, a lost cause.  Hopefully, the former, but in either case, those three people are well beyond the point of having to figure out this kind of theme, and are making the effort to help someone with lesser skills.

You, my friend, are what they call a gadfly.

@Matt

I know it’s a lost cause responding to you but I really am trying to help. When I asked “if you had checked the column” I meant it seriously; if that was the case then that would have been my first suggestion. Some people do comment without reading it. If the answer was “I did but I still didn’t understand it” then I would try to help that way. And if the answer is “I don’t want to understand any more, the fact that I didn’t understand it makes it a bad theme” then I would simply say I disagree and leave him to his opinion. As it is it wasn’t clear from the post whether he wanted help or on what.

I agree with Steve L at this point I just think you like to stir up trouble for no reason and create bad feelings where none was intended. Not sure why.

@Matt
I ask lots of help with clues and have never felt condescended to. 
I'm with Barry, Steve, SP and Francis here.

@Al  in Pittsburgh

ha ha yes a Vietnamese orthodox affair!

I only wish the deer hunting scenes were shot around here, too, and not in the Cascades in Washington. But we've been whining about that since 1978.

@john ezra

Oh c'mon, stick to your guns. Your solving experience was what it was. If a constructor wants to be mollycoddled, they should not submit puzzles for international publication.

I personally flinched not only at the Monday difficulty on Wednesday (the editors' fault) but also at ESP being called a skill, and a helpful one at that (possibly down to the editors too, I suppose...)

@john ezra

But he submitted the puzzle here, not to a magazine for teens, and he should be treated just as any other constructor, IMO. Also, there is something condescending in taking his age into account. I know I hated that, as a young adult - "You did great (for a person your age)!"

I wasn't telling you what to do, btw. It was just a suggestion.

@SP
I always go back and try my hand at solving past puzzles when people recommend them. That one came in about 7 minutes longer than my average Friday, and about 7 minutes shorter than my average Saturday. I don't know if that proves anything, because the things I remember from those olden days seem to counterbalance the things I don't yet know from the popular names and slang of today. 

At any rate, it was a fun solve. Thanks.

